    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a museum-grade 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), a definitive example of the analog driving experience. Powered by the M96/03 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six featuring VarioCam Plus, this unit provides exceptional throttle response and a linear power band. The G96 6-speed manual transaxle offers crisp, positive engagement with no synchro hesitation. This specimen features a documented LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a recent clean borescope report, ensuring peak internal health. The chassis remains taut, retaining factory-spec suspension geometry and bushing integrity. Finished in Arctic Silver over a flawless cabin, this is a turn-key investment for the discerning purist seeking mechanical perfection.",
